# {{{skill_name}}}

## Connection

- **Endpoint:** `{{{server_origin}}}/api/agent/skill`
- **Method:** `POST`
- **Content-Type:** `application/json`
- **Authorization:** `Bearer {{{auth_token}}}`

## Request Format

```json
{
  "tool": "<tool_name>",
  "parameters": { ... }
}
```

## Response Format

Most tools return a JSON object directly. For example:
```json
{ "ok": true }
```

Image tools (`take_screenshot`, `download_photo`, `mark_coordinates`) return MCP content format:
```json
{ "content": [{ "type": "image", "data": "<base64>", "mimeType": "image/png" }] }
```

Error responses: `{ "error": "<message>" }`

## Coordinate Verification (REQUIRED)

Before tapping, double-tapping, long-pressing, or dragging on the device screen, you **MUST** follow this workflow:

1. Call `get_device_control_size` to learn the valid coordinate range.
2. Call `mark_coordinates` with your intended coordinates to visually verify they hit the correct target.
3. Only after confirming the crosshair markers are positioned correctly, perform the action (`tap`, `double_tap`, `touch_and_hold`, `drag`).

Never guess coordinates without verifying them first ‚Äî skipping this workflow risks tapping the wrong element.

## Tools

### Device Management

#### `list_devices`
List all connected iOS devices with their status.
- Parameters: _(none)_
- Returns: `{ "devices": [{ "udid", "connected", "linked", "tunnelReady", "wdaState", "mainPort?", "mjpegPort?" }] }`

#### `get_device_prefs`
Get preferences for a device.
- `udid` (string, required) ‚Äî Device UDID

#### `set_device_prefs`
Update preferences for a device.
- `udid` (string, required) ‚Äî Device UDID
- `alwaysAwake` (boolean, optional) ‚Äî Keep the device screen on

### Screen Interaction

#### `get_device_control_size`
Get the device control coordinate space. All coordinate-based tools use this range.
- `udid` (string, required) ‚Äî Device UDID
- Returns: `{ "width", "height" }`

#### `mark_coordinates`
Visually verify coordinates before performing device control actions. Returns one annotated screenshot per coordinate. Each image has a full-screen crosshair: a horizontal line spanning the full width and a vertical line spanning the full height. The point where these two lines intersect is the EXACT coordinate that will be acted on. A small numbered badge sits at the intersection. Lines use per-pixel color negation for visibility. To verify: look ONLY at the intersection point and confirm it lands on the intended UI element.
- `udid` (string, required) ‚Äî Device UDID
- `coordinates` (array, required) ‚Äî Array of `{ x, y }` in device control points
- Returns: MCP content format with one image per coordinate

#### `tap`
Tap at a coordinate on the device screen. Coordinates are in device control points (call get_device_control_size first, then mark_coordinates to visually verify the target before tapping).
- `udid` (string, required) ‚Äî Device UDID
- `x` (number, required) ‚Äî X coordinate
- `y` (number, required) ‚Äî Y coordinate

#### `double_tap`
Double-tap at a coordinate on the device screen. Coordinates are in device control points (call get_device_control_size first, then mark_coordinates to visually verify the target before double-tapping).
- `udid` (string, required) ‚Äî Device UDID
- `x` (number, required) ‚Äî X coordinate
- `y` (number, required) ‚Äî Y coordinate

#### `touch_and_hold`
Long-press at a coordinate on the device screen. Coordinates are in device control points (call get_device_control_size first, then mark_coordinates to visually verify the target before pressing).
- `udid` (string, required) ‚Äî Device UDID
- `x` (number, required) ‚Äî X coordinate
- `y` (number, required) ‚Äî Y coordinate
- `duration` (number, required) ‚Äî Hold duration in seconds

#### `drag`
Drag (swipe) from one coordinate to another on the device screen. Coordinates are in device control points (call get_device_control_size first, then mark_coordinates to visually verify start and end points before dragging).
- `udid` (string, required) ‚Äî Device UDID
- `fromX` (number, required) ‚Äî Start X coordinate
- `fromY` (number, required) ‚Äî Start Y coordinate
- `toX` (number, required) ‚Äî End X coordinate
- `toY` (number, required) ‚Äî End Y coordinate
- `duration` (number, required) ‚Äî Drag duration in seconds

#### `type_text`
Type text on the device (requires a focused text field). If you need to tap a text field first, follow the coordinate verification workflow: get_device_control_size ‚Üí mark_coordinates ‚Üí tap, then type_text.
- `udid` (string, required) ‚Äî Device UDID
- `text` (string, required) ‚Äî Text to type

#### `get_screen_size`
Get the device screen dimensions in points.
- `udid` (string, required) ‚Äî Device UDID

#### `take_screenshot`
Take a screenshot of the device screen (returns base64 PNG).
- `udid` (string, required) ‚Äî Device UDID

### Device Control

#### `go_home`
Press the home button / go to home screen.
- `udid` (string, required) ‚Äî Device UDID

#### `lock_device`
Lock the device screen.
- `udid` (string, required) ‚Äî Device UDID

#### `unlock_device`
Unlock the device screen.
- `udid` (string, required) ‚Äî Device UDID

#### `is_locked`
Check if the device screen is locked.
- `udid` (string, required) ‚Äî Device UDID

### App Management

#### `launch_app`
Launch an app by bundle identifier.
- `udid` (string, required) ‚Äî Device UDID
- `bundleId` (string, required) ‚Äî App bundle identifier (e.g. com.apple.mobilesafari)

#### `terminate_app`
Terminate a running app by bundle identifier.
- `udid` (string, required) ‚Äî Device UDID
- `bundleId` (string, required) ‚Äî App bundle identifier

#### `list_apps`
List installed apps on the device (User apps + curated System apps).
- `udid` (string, required) ‚Äî Device UDID
- Returns: `{ "apps": [{ "bundleId", "name" }] }`

### Photos

#### `list_photos`
List photos on the device camera roll with pagination.
- `udid` (string, required) ‚Äî Device UDID
- `limit` (number, optional) ‚Äî Number of photos to return (default: 50)
- `cursor` (string, optional) ‚Äî Pagination cursor from a previous response

#### `download_photo`
Download a photo from the device (returns base64 image).
- `udid` (string, required) ‚Äî Device UDID
- `path` (string, required) ‚Äî Photo path on device (from list_photos, must start with /DCIM/)
